sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Gateway Layer<br/>(Kuadrant/Authorino)<br/>Envoy ext_authz
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP RESP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant Infer as Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d / vLLM)
    participant GCsvc as Garbage Collector

    Note over Client,Infer: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/files<br/>Upload JSONL input file
    GW->>GW: ext_authz: authenticate<br/>Append X-MaaS-Username
    GW->>API: Forward with tenant header
    API->>S3: Store input file content<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
    API->>PG: Create file metadata record<br/>TCP/5432, connection URL creds
    API-->>Client: 200 OK (file_id)

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches<br/>input_file_id, model, endpoint
    GW->>GW: ext_authz: authenticate
    GW->>API: Forward with tenant header
    API->>PG: Create batch record (validating)<br/>TCP/5432
    API->>Redis: Enqueue job to priority queue<br/>TCP/6379, sorted set by SLO
    API-->>Client: 200 OK (batch_id, status: validating)

    Note over Client,Infer: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing

    loop Poll interval (5s)
        Proc->>Redis: BZPOPMIN from priority queue<br/>TCP/6379
    end
    Redis-->>Proc: Job payload (batch_id, priority)

    Proc->>PG: Read batch + file metadata<br/>TCP/5432
    Proc->>S3: Download input JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
    S3-->>Proc: Input file content

    Proc->>Proc: Pre-process: parse JSONL,<br/>build per-model execution plans

    Proc->>PG: Update status: in_progress<br/>TCP/5432

    loop For each inference request (up to 50,000)
        Proc->>Proc: Acquire semaphores:<br/>per-model -> global
        Proc->>Infer: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP(S), Bearer token or mTLS<br/>x-slo-ttft-ms, x-gateway-inference-objective
        Infer-->>Proc: Inference response
        Proc->>Proc: Release semaphores
        Proc->>Redis: Update progress counter<br/>TCP/6379
    end

    Proc->>S3: Upload output JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+, AWS IAM
    opt Errors occurred
        Proc->>S3: Upload error JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443
    end
    Proc->>PG: Update status: completed<br/>Set output_file_id, error_file_id<br/>TCP/5432

    Note over Client,Infer: Flow 3: Status Check & Result Retrieval

    Client->>GW: GET /v1/batches/{batch_id}
    GW->>API: Forward with tenant header
    API->>PG: Read batch metadata<br/>TCP/5432
    API->>Redis: Read progress status<br/>TCP/6379
    API-->>Client: Batch status with progress counts

    Client->>GW: GET /v1/files/{output_file_id}/content
    GW->>API: Forward with tenant header
    API->>S3: Download output file<br/>HTTPS/443
    API-->>Client: Stream output JSONL

    Note over GCsvc,S3: Flow 4: Garbage Collection (every 30m)

    loop GC interval (30m)
        GCsvc->>PG: Query expired batches and files<br/>TCP/5432
        PG-->>GCsvc: Expired items list
        GCsvc->>S3: Delete expired file content<br/>HTTPS/443
        GCsvc->>PG: Delete expired metadata records<br/>TCP/5432
    end
